DIGEST
SB 221 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Boudreaux
Proposed law requires Medicaid to cover treatment-in-place services provided by ambulance
providers.
Proposed law defines a "treatment-in-place service" as an encounter between an ambulance
provider and beneficiary which takes place in response to a 911 call where an assessment
or treatment is provided by the ambulance provider to the beneficiary but transport of the
beneficiary is not performed.
Proposed law requires treatment-in-place services to be covered by the associated basic life
support, emergency base rate, or the advanced life support, Level 1 emergency base rate
provided for in the Medicaid fee schedule, depending on level of response and services
rendered.
Proposed law requires the La. Dept. of Health to promulgate rules to implement the
provisions of proposed law.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 40:1132)
